<text>Damp

&lt; Previous | Index | Next &gt;

The damp command slows down the currently selected particles through frictional forces propotional to their velocities but acting in the opposite directions. (To see how to add a damping force to a particle without using scripts, see this section.)

Syntax:

damp [friction coefficient]

where [friction coefficient] is a non-negative number that will be the friction coefficient.

Here is an example of using the damp command to slow down an atom:

 

 
